Leather
=============

An experiment taking an MVCish approach to Express using CoffeeScript, Eco and MongoDB.


Try it out:
============

**Things you'll need**

* [nodejs](http://nodejs.org/) - I recommend installing it with [homebrew](http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/) via `brew install node`
* [npm](http://npmjs.org/) - `curl http://npmjs.org/install.sh | sh`

**Download the source**

	$ git clone git@github.com:caseyohara/leather.git

**Install Dependencies**	

	$ cd leather
	$ npm install -d

**Fire up the server**

	$ node server.js

Now point your browser to [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)


